I found on my travels to this pull request a better understanding of this crates architecture. I think further improvements could be made refactoring warp bindings into a generic http/http_body abstraction for which warp or Axum or tower bindings could be made. However I was not smart enough to accomplish this my spare time.

I hope this is some form useful.

```rust
use axum::prelude::*;
use axum::routing::BoxRoute;
use cloudevents::Event;
use http::StatusCode;

fn app() -> BoxRoute<Body> {
    route(
        "/",
        post(|event: Event| async move {
            println!("received cloudevent {}", &event);
            (StatusCode::OK, event)
        }),
    )
    .boxed()
}

#[tokio::main]
async fn main() {
    axum::Server::bind(&"0.0.0.0:3000".parse().unwrap())
        .serve(app().into_make_service())
        .await
        .unwrap();
}
```

